en_134633_0	The Ministry of Provincial Councils and Local Government states that measures has been taken to dispose 2500 tons of garbage which was accumulated in the Colombo District after the recent flooding.
en_134633_1	The Ministry states the disposed garbage was dumped at Kolonnawa dumping site.
en_134633_2	Five hundred personals from Army, Police and Civil Defense Forces has been deployed.
en_134633_3	By now the following areas Kolonnawa, Meethotamulla, Kotikawatta, Mulleriyawa, Angoda, Gothatuwa, Sedawatta and Wellampitiya have been cleared of garbage.
